Our contribution (LP-0002 anonymous M-of-N multisig)
----------------------------------------------------
The following paths are authored as part of this LP-0002 submission and are NOT part of
upstream LEZ v0.2.0-rc5. They add an anonymous M-of-N multisig program to LEZ:

  programs/msig/core/src/lib.rs
      msig_core: depth-5 Merkle member scheme, MsigInstruction
      (CreateProposal, Approve, Enroll, Execute, InitTreasury), domain-separated
      leaf/nullifier hashing, account layouts.

  test_program_methods/guest/src/bin/msig.rs
      the on-chain msig guest.

  examples/program_deployment/src/msig_demo.rs
      shared LP-0002 demo fixture.

  examples/program_deployment/src/bin/run_deploy.rs
  examples/program_deployment/src/bin/run_enroll.rs
  examples/program_deployment/src/bin/run_init_treasury.rs
  examples/program_deployment/src/bin/run_create_proposal.rs
  examples/program_deployment/src/bin/run_approve.rs
  examples/program_deployment/src/bin/run_execute.rs
  examples/program_deployment/src/bin/run_assert_state.rs
      LP-0002 client runners (run_assert_state is the demo's read-only green/red gate).

  msig tests in lee/state_machine/src/state.rs and
  lee/state_machine/src/privacy_preserving_transaction/circuit.rs
      added msig public-path / bootstrap / compose / approve tests.

  LP-0002 packaging:
      README-LP0002.md
      NOTICE
      scripts/lp0002-demo-rc5.sh
      scripts/lp0002-resume-rc5.sh
      scripts/lp0002-testnet-run.sh
      docs/LP-0002-solution.md
      docs/lp0002-benchmarks.md
      docs/lp0002-reliability.md
      idl/lp0002-msig.idl.json
      .github/workflows/lp0002-ci.yml

